<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99435172282535></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99435172282535><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=7&mid=99435172282535>What to do?</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jul 5th 12:48 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I&#8217;m VERY new to this additive game, so forgive my ignorance...<br><br>First, a little about my character:<br><br>I'm a High-elf Cleric, and I just made 10th level.  Right now, I'm fighting orcs in and around Crushbone (sometimes solo, but usually with a ranger friend).  I was turning in the Crushbone belts for XP, but someone told me that I could sell them to other players for 1pp each and buy better armor, also from other players, with the proceeds (I was wearing tattered armor and leather from the shops).   Now, I have lots of banded armor but I am almost to my weight limit.<br><br>Now for my questions:<br><br>How can I raise my strength so I can carry more weight?<br>I was told that there are packs that reduce the weight of items within them.  Where and how do I get one of these packs?<br>At my level and location, are there any quests I could do to get better items?  (I looked in the quest area, but the information is a little overwhelming).  Also, is there any good items that monsters drop that I could find and use?<br><br>Thanks for your help!<br><br><br>PS.  I love running a cleric!  It&#8217;s fun to hang around the orc lift or orc hill and heal strangers.  Most don&#8217;t even thank me (that&#8217;s ok), but many do and a simple &#8220;thank you&#8221; from an appreciative player is much more satisfying than killing a computer-run monster.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
