<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9944506595241></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9944506595241><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=7&mid=9944506595241>RE: What to do?</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jul 6th 4:17 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I disagree with Kad. Wis is your key to success, period, as a Cleric.<br><br>What you need to do is get one or two good +str items (i recommend rings at your level, 2 +2 Str rings are fairly cheap) to hold you off till your armor gets lighter.<br><br>Also fork out the 100-125pp for a Velium Round Shield. It's something like 10 AC, +10 vs cold, for only POINT 5 weight. Yes, that was .5 weight. Given most other shields weigh in the 8-12 range for similiar stats you can't go wrong, plus it looks REAL cool all see through and runes and all.<br>When i bought mine it kept my weight down as a DaEl cleric till i got to the 30's and could afford +str/+wis items and could upgrade to charred guardian shield.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
