<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99346815214035></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99346815214035><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=7&mid=99346815214035>RE: AC Vs. Wisdom</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=13385><span id=Scholar>Neptunis</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>95 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jun 25th 7:22 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.04]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Definative, no, but I can add some insight.  <br><br>At level 21 especially until 24 mana is everything.  Every additional heal is important to the groups survival, and your channeling skill is not yet high enough to be reliable.  Once you get Greater Heal your life gets much easier.  <br><br>AC does not add to mana but it does do some very nice things.  First, as you pointed out it keeps you alive (cheer).  If you die before the tank can taunt off the MOB the group dies.  Actually this is a secondary benefit for Cleric Armor, what AC does is reduce damage to a "you have regained your concentration" level.  High AC lets you cast more while getting hit.  Defense, dodge, stun, roots all work to allow the Cleric to keep healing while he or she is on the top of the Agro List.<br><br>Now a little bit about Wisdom.  Wisdom does control how much mana you have total, but how often are you ever FULL OF MANA during a grouping period.  Since you are normally somewhere short of full, how much you have at full isn't that important.  I usually tell my group when I have 2 heals left I "LOW MANA", when I get to 1 heal remaining I'm "VERY LOW MANA"  and then I'm "MEDDING FOR HEALS".  At that pint does it matter what my max capacity mana is?  Probably not.  I try to stay around 50% mana, if I get more I'll buff, when I drop below I stop topping off tanks and become super mana efficient to get to 50%.  <br><br>Total Wisdom/mana isn't something to live and die over, being able to cast while a white MOB is wacking at you is.  If AC reduces hits (not bashes) to around 20-40 damage I can often channel through and cast, over that and I'm almost always disrupted.  I hope this helps you out a little.<br><br>Vildaar Darkmender<br>lvl 35 DE Cleric<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
